A lorry was on Wednesday offloaded by angry youths at Kanyonga in Mwingi after it was found transporting charcoal to Nairobi. Charcoal burning has been banned in Kitui county with youths torching vehicles found transporting the commodity. On Wedensday, they refrained from setting the lorry ablaze but looted all the charcoal it was carrying. The youths said their actions were in line with the ban imposed by Governor Charity Ngilu. On Tuesday, a Probox was set ablaze in Mwingi town after it was found transporting charcoal. Police in the area have promised to effect the ban.   